---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---

<SiteLayout
	title="Community"
	description="Contribute, discuss, and find FlightGear resources related to OpenAttitude."
>
	<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 sm:py-16">
		<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-4xl">Community</h1>
		<p class="mt-4 text-lg text-slate-400">
			OpenAttitude spans a <strong class="text-slate-200">panel application</strong> and many small
			<strong class="text-slate-200">npm packages</strong>. Bug reports and changes should go to the repository
			that owns the code you are modifying (fgpanel vs a specific <code class="text-cyan-300/80"
				>@openattitude/*</code
			> package).
		</p>
		<div class="mt-10 space-y-8 text-slate-400">
			<section>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">FlightGear</h2>
				<p class="mt-2">
					For sim configuration, aircraft, and multiplayer topics, the <strong class="text-slate-300"
						>FlightGear</strong
					> community forums and wiki remain the primary hub.
				</p>
				<ul class="mt-3 list-inside list-disc space-y-1">
					<li>
						<a
							href="https://www.flightgear.org/"
							class="text-cyan-400 no-underline hover:underline"
							target="_blank"
							rel="noopener noreferrer">flightgear.org</a
						>
					</li>
				</ul>
			</section>
			<section>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Packages on npm</h2>
				<p class="mt-2">
					Instrument releases are published under the <code class="rounded bg-slate-800 px-1.5 text-cyan-300/80"
						>@openattitude</code
					> scope. Use npm issues or the source repository linked from each package page for library-specific
					feedback.
				</p>
				<p class="mt-3">
					<a
						href="https://www.npmjs.com/search?q=%40openattitude"
						class="font-medium text-cyan-400 no-underline hover:underline"
						target="_blank"
						rel="noopener noreferrer">Search @openattitude on npm →</a
					>
				</p>
			</section>
		</div>
	</div>
</SiteLayout>
